cmd/cli/tests/test_metadata_service.py::TestAgentMetadata::test_agent_metadata_invalid_build_mode -v`\n33: \n34: - [x] **T1.4**: Implement `port` field validator\n35:   - Purpose: Validate port is in range 1-65535\n36:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/metadata_service.py:50-55`\n37:   - Verification: `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_metadata_service.py::TestAgentMetadata::test_agent_metadata_invalid_port_low -v`\n38: \n39: ### Phase 2: MetadataOptions Dataclass (ST-2)\n40: \n41: - [x] **T2.1**: Implement `MetadataOptions` dataclass with all CLI options fields\n42:   - Purpose: Define dataclass for mapping command-line arguments to metadata fields\n43:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/models/pack_models.py:6-21`\n44:   - Verification: `python -c \"from agentcube.models.pack_models import MetadataOptions; print(MetadataOptions.__dataclass_fields__)\"`\n45: \n46: - [x] **T2.2**: Implement `MetadataOptions.from_options()` factory method\n47:   - Purpose: Create MetadataOptions from dict filtering None values\n48:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/models/pack_models.py:23-26`\n49:   - Verification: `python -c \"from agentcube.models.pack_models import MetadataOptions; opt = MetadataOptions.from_options({'agent_name': 'test', 'port': 8080}); print(opt.agent_name)\"`\n50: \n51: ### Phase 3: MetadataService Core Methods (ST-3)\n52: \n53: - [x] **T3.1**: Implement `MetadataService.__init__` with verbose flag\n54:   - Purpose: Initialize service with verbose flag for logging control\n55:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/metadata_service.py:59-60`\n56:   - Verification: `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_metadata_service.py::TestMetadataService::test_metadata_service_load_agent_metadata_yaml -v`\n57: \n58: - [x] **T3.2**: Implement `load_metadata()` with fallback filename list\n59:   - Purpose: Load metadata from workspace, falling back through ['agent_metadata.yaml', 'agent.yaml', 'metadata.yaml']\n60:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/metadata_service.py:62-72`\n61:   - Verification: `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_metadata_service.py::TestMetadataService::test_metadata_service_load_fallback_agent_yaml -v`\n62: \n63: - [x] **T3.3**: Implement `save_metadata()` with YAML serialization settings\n64:   - Purpose: Save metadata to agent_metadata.yaml with exclude_none, indent=2, no flow style\n65:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/metadata_service.py:74-79`\n66:   - Verification: `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_metadata_service.py::TestMetadataService::test_metadata_service_save_excludes_none -v`\n67: \n68: - [ ] **T3.4**: Implement `update_metadata()` method\n69:   - Purpose: Load, apply updates dict, save, and return new AgentMetadata\n70:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/metadata_service.py`\n71:   - Verification: `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_metadata_service.py::TestMetadataService::test_metadata_service_update -v`\n72: \n73: - [ ] **T3.5**: Implement `validate_workspace()` method\n74:   - Purpose: Validate workspace structure and language-specific requirements\n75:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/metadata_service.py`\n76:   - Verification: `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_metadata_service.py::TestMetadataService::test_validate_workspace_python -v`\n77: \n78: - [ ] **T3.6**: Implement `_validate_python_workspace()` helper\n79:   - Purpose: Check for at least one *.py file in workspace root\n80:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/metadata_service.py`\n81:   - Verification: `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_metadata_service.py::TestMetadataService::test_validate_python_workspace_has_py -v`\n82: \n83: - [ ] **T3.7**: Implement `_validate_java_workspace()` helper\n84:   - Purpose: Check for pom.xml in workspace\n85:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/metadata_service.py`\n86:   - Verification: `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_metadata_service.py::TestMetadataService::test_validate_java_workspace_has_pom -v`\n87: \n88: ### Phase 4: Comprehensive Unit Tests (ST-4)\n89: \n90: - [x] **T4.1**: Test AgentMetadata valid creation\n91:   - Purpose: Verify AgentMetada